      "lesson title": "Firmware-Level AI Risks",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces the security risks that arise when artificial intelligence is embedded directly into hardware components such as chipsets, microcontrollers, and firmware layers. You will explore how AI operating at this low level of a system can create vulnerabilities that are difficult to detect, patch, or remove compared to software-based threats. The lesson covers practical examples of how malicious or compromised firmware-level AI can be exploited, and why traditional security tools often struggle to address these risks. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of why firmware-level AI deserves special attention in any security strategy, and what steps organisations can begin to take to protect themselves.",
