          "slidecontent": "• Hidden code embedded in firmware during manufacture or supply chain handling\n• Designed to activate silently, often triggered by specific conditions or remote commands\n• Can bypass security software entirely, since it operates below the operating system\n• Extremely difficult to detect\n• AI accelerators and smart chips increasingly targeted due to their privileged hardware access\n• Once installed, removal often requires physical replacement of the affected component"
