          "slidetitle": "Patching AI Firmware Vulnerabilities",
          "subtitle": "Closing the Gaps Before Threats Escalate",
          "slidecontent": "• Firmware patches for AI components often require full device restarts, making timely updates harder to schedule\n• Vendors may release fixes slowly\n• Prioritising critical vulnerabilities over minor ones helps teams focus limited patching resources effectively\n• Automated patch management tools can flag outdated AI firmware across large fleets of devices\n• Testing patches in a controlled environment before wide deployment reduces the risk of breaking existing functionality\n• Keeping a clear record of patch history supports audits and helps identify gaps in coverage"
